       page content, leaving a gap where the body's background peeks
       through. Letting the container size itself to its content and
       scroll like a normal page is what actually avoids that gap in
       every case. */
    .dashboard-container { display: block; height: auto; min-height: 100vh; min-height: 100dvh; overflow: visible; }

    .mobile-menu-btn { display: flex; }
